        <h3>Project Overview</h3>
        <p>TThis project was my final assignment at UCSD within the HCI (Human Computer Interaction) department. The goal of the project was to reach out to a local business and offer to completely redesign their existing website. The scope of the project was only to focus on the redesign, not actually building the site for them. We could offer that, but only once the project was finished.</p>
        <p>I chose to reach out to Sailors Grave Tattoo Gallery since I had just gotten a tattoo from them. Seeing as tattooing is inherently design centric, I figured it would be a unique project to combine tattooing and web design. They were enthusiastically receptive and were a fantastic business to work with.
        </p>
        <h3>UX Process</h3>
        <p>Before beginning my design I wanted to first interview the shop owner to set a foundation for his expectation of the site redesign. I categorized the interview into several sections:
            <ul>
                <li>Analysis of current site</li>
                <li>Desires for future site</li>
                <li>Brand | Audience | Image</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        
        <p>Having established the  expectations of the shop owner,  I then set out to understand the various types of customers. I conducted surveys at the tattoo shop over the course of several weekends and was able to categorize the majority of interviewees into three types of user personas:
            <ul>
                <li>Customers with tattoos</li>
                <li>Customers without tattoos</li>
                <li>Customers looking to cover-up an existing tattoo</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
