        <h3>High Fidelity Wireframes</h3>
        <p>Moving on to creating high fidelity wireframes for the site, I first wanted to establish a few stylistic elements such as a color palette and font combinations to use. </p>
        <p>For the color palette, the shop owner had given me a paint sample of the new color he was planning to paint the shop with. With that color bring the primary color, I was then able to choose several accent colors to compliment it. I wanted to keep the palette relatively light and neutral. So many tattoo shop websites have dark color palettes which I find uninviting. I figured by utilizing lighter and neutral colors, it would give the impression of being a more welcoming and inviting space.</p>
        <p>For the font combination, I wanted a bold but not too aggressive main heading. I felt Oswald Medium best fit that constraint and Oswald Light provided a less aggressive subheading. As for the body, Open Sans complimented Oswald well. It provided a neutral, yet familiar style making it legible and easy to read.</p>
        <img alt="Style Guide for SGTG" src="/images/sgtg/style.png">
        <p>With the the style guide established, I was able to focus on setting the the appropriate layouts for the various pages, paying close attention to the artist profile page. I wanted to utilize a fair amount of padding and white space to help highlight the artists and their artwork. </p>
    </div>

