        <h3>Project Reflection</h3>
        <p>Looking back, I would have liked to develop the site myself but given the time constraints of the class and project I was ok giving the finished designs over to the shop owner and letting him use them however he saw fit.</p>
        <p>However, being my first design project, this was a tremendous learning experience. It gave me valuable insight into the immense work you have to put in to great a website. Everything from conducting user surveys and creating user personas to selecting font combinations allowed me see how all of those factors play a vital role in the ultimate design of not only a website but a product. </p>
